Conclusion:
RoboGrip X5 is a collaborative project developed by a team of four members from the Mechanical and CSD departments. 
The project demonstrates the integration of hardware and software using an Arduino Uno R3, five servo motors, and a 5V external power supply to perform pick-and-place operations.

As a CSD student, my contribution focused on developing and handling the coding part, including the Python GUI and Arduino programming required to control the robotic arm.
This project highlights effective teamwork and practical implementation of automation concepts.
